            <thetext>Selecting or deselecting tests in the Test Runner&#39;s HTML view can take very long in old browsers. For example, for the qx.Website test suite (173 tests), (de)selecting all tests takes almost eight seconds in IE8 on our Win XP testing machine.

Profiling shows that the most time is spent on searching the test suite model for the objects representing the individual tests. Since we only need those to actually run the selected tests, we could defer the lookup until the user presses the &quot;Run&quot; button. That would at least speed up filtering and selecting subsets of the suite.</thetext>
